12-month contract + strong extensions
Hybrid (Mon/Tues/Thurs onsite Melbourne CBD) + 2x days from home 

Join this large transformational project, backed by over $400M in funding and running through to the end of 2027. 

We’re looking for a Change Analyst who’s excited by meaningful work and the opportunity to help shape a maturing Change function from the ground up.

Working closely with Simon so he can stay focused on high-level program strategy
Why this role is exciting:

Senior Data Engineer  
The Opportunity:
One of Australia’s leading QSR brands seeks a talented Senior Data Engineer to take ownership of a Snowflake and Azure Data Factory landscape that sits behind millions of customer orders.
  
This is a tech-first, AI-driven business with a close partnership with Microsoft, where experimenting with new AI tools is part of how you work, not something you do on the side.
  
You will join a sharp, seven-person data integration team, working alongside a Data Integration Manager and a dedicated architecture function. Your job is to transform raw, messy data into trusted pipelines that fuel real-time insights, better customer experiences, and more intelligent decisions across every corner of the business.
  
What you’ll do:

Collaborate with stakeholders and the Data Integration Manager to define requirements and deliver projects on schedule.
Embed data compliance, including GDPR and PII handling in Snowflake, into everything you design
Design, build and run scalable data integration solutions and pipelines across internal and external systems.
Orchestrate, cleanse and transform data so it is reliable, secure and ready for analytics and product teams.
Set and refine standards, patterns and best practices for data integration across the platform.
Collaborate with data engineers, software engineers and BI developers to deliver end-to-end solutions.
Mentor junior team members and help lift the capability of the wider data team
Partner with BI Operations on releases, change control and production readiness
Keep documentation sharp and up to date, with accurate time logging against project work  
What you bring:

Full Australian citizenship or permanent residency
5+ years of hands-on experience with Snowflake and Azure Data Factory
IT degree or 5+ years in a data engineering or data-focused role
5+ years using T SQL and SQL Server (2008 or later) with strong ETL skills, including SSIS and ADF
Solid data modelling and deep dive analysis skills
Experience with cloud-based data platforms and modern data architectures
Practical experience with JavaScript or Python, plus REST APIs and at least one OOP language such as C# or Java
Data visualisation experience with tools such as Grafana, Power BI or SSRS
Working knowledge of GDPR and secure handling of PII in Snowflake
Comfortable working in Agile environments with tools like Jira and Azure DevOps
Familiar with structured change management processes
Clear communication, strong organisation and high attention to detail
Curiosity about new tech and a track record of using AI tools to move faster and ship better work
Apply now or contact us for more information.

Initial 18-mth contract with possible extension paying approx. $980/day
Brisbane CBD Location with flexibility to WFH 2 days per week
Change Manager with experience in data, analytics, or digital platform transformations
Our client, Department of Education, are currently seeking a Change Manager (Data) for an initial 18 month contract to join their EQIP Program. 

The Branch

The Strategy and Performance Branch, sits within the Strategic Policy and External Relations Division of the Department of Education (DoE) and coordinates the portfolio’s contribution to whole-of-government and departmental strategy, planning, governance, reporting and performance management processes and initiatives.
The Performance Monitoring and Reporting Unit delivers performance, business intelligence, monitoring, measurement and reporting products to support DoE and Queensland Government priorities and national agendas. The Unit has commenced the Education Queensland Insights Platform (EQIP) Program and is building a team of experts to support this high-profile initiative.

Program Overview:

EQIP is a transformational, multi-year program establishing DoE’s enterprise data platform and strengthening data governance to enable trusted, timely insights for schools, regions and corporate.

Position overview

We are seeking a Change Manager with experience in data, analytics, or digital platform transformations. You will drive the people-side of change for the Enterprise Data Platform (EDP) and Data Governance roll-out—shaping messages on privacy-by-design, approvals to copy vs use data, and new ways of working across central and federated data and analytics teams. The role focuses on adoption, behaviours, and capability uplift so teams can safely and confidently onboard and use governed data.

Tasks and activities

Develop a Change & Adoption Plan specific to EDP and Data Governance (roles, RACI).
Coordinate onboarding communications (Source-to-Insight, ingestion approvals, use-case approvals, stewards/custodians) with the wider EQIP Team.
Create how-to playbooks and concise guidance for analysts and product owners (e.g., “consuming governed data,” “retiring legacy reports”).
Run targeted readiness sessions for branches/regions (quick-win use cases, what stays local vs what centralises).
Stand up a change champion network in key areas (Finance, HR, Infrastructure, Regions) to localise messages and surface issues early.
Partner with Data Governance to embed glossary, definitions, and standards in communications; support rollout of Purview awareness (discovery vs data movement).
Define and monitor adoption metrics (use of governed data products, retirement of shadow pipelines, training completion, sentiment).
Provide ELT/Board updates on change risks, mitigations, and adoption progress; align with benefits realisation.
Experience and skills

Change manager delivering large public-sector or regulated-industry programs with experience in data, analytics, or digital platform transformations
Demonstrated ability to translate complex change into plain English for executive and frontline audiences.
Strong stakeholder engagement across executive and senior leadership, and unionised environments; confident preparing and/or facilitating workshops.
Experience preparing material for ministerial/executive governance.
Excellent writing, editing, and visual storytelling skills.
To submit your application, in strict confidence, please submit your resume in Word Format using the appropriate link quoting reference No. 247488.  Should you require further information please email kristy.coulter@hudson.com

Your interest will be treated in the strictest of confidence.

From humble beginnings in 2011, Evolution Mining is now a leading gold producer, operating six mines across Australia and Canada. Enacting our vision to be inspired people creating a premier global gold company, we are indeed a bold team with a bright future. Our operational diversity offers our employees access to many experiences and career opportunities within the one company. So, whether you choose to work at one of our underground or open pit operations, explore for our future as part of our Discovery team, or join our Group Office, we know you'll have a bright future with us.

At our Group Office

Working in our Group Office, you have a front row seat to our vision and are a part of the bold, inspired teams who are engineering its success. We're an agile, entrepreneurial company and we value smart people and creative thinking. When you work with us, you'll always have the opportunity to progress from where you started. Based in the Sydney CBD, our people work with teams located across Australia and Canada which makes for interesting work and countless ways to learn and grow.

Your Benefits

At Evolution, we support, develop and reward everyone who chooses to be a part of our bright future. Your benefits include relocation support assistance, novated car leasing, life insurance and income protection, short term incentives, referral bonuses, recognition program, study assistance, discounted health insurance and wellness days. 

 

This role will work a 5/2 roster from the Sydney office with 2 days WFH option available

We understand that flexible work means something different to everyone and encourage you to have a conversation about the flexible work options available.

About the Role

As the Data Governance Lead, you will play a pivotal role in shaping and embedding Evolution Mining's data governance framework across the organisation. Reporting to the Group Manager - Enterprise Data & Analytics, you'll be responsible for ensuring data is trusted, well-managed, and effectively used to support business decisions.

This role is both strategic and operational. You'll design and implement governance policies, establish ownership and stewardship structures, and lead the rollout of tools and processes such as data catalogues and quality rules. You'll work closely with stakeholders across corporate and site teams to drive adoption, build capability, and foster a culture of accountability and data fluency.

Key focus areas include:

Delivering a fit-for-purpose governance framework
Driving stakeholder engagement and communication
Overseeing data quality and compliance
Building governance capability and culture

Success in this role will be measured by the adoption of governance practices, improvements in data quality, stakeholder engagement, and the integration of governance into business decision-making.

About You

You are a strategic yet hands-on data governance professional with a passion for turning principles into practice. With a strong foundation in data management disciplines—such as metadata, data quality, and master data—you bring a pragmatic approach to embedding governance across complex environments. You've successfully implemented governance frameworks in medium-to-large organisations and are confident navigating both corporate IT and operational technology landscapes.

To succeed in this role, you'll bring the following ten things to this role:

Proven experience implementing data governance frameworks in medium-to-large organisations
Strong stakeholder engagement skills across all levels, including executive leadership
Excellent communication abilities - you can translate technical concepts into business value
Hands-on experience with data governance tools (e.g., Kada, Alation) and practices
Deep understanding of data management disciplines including metadata, data quality, and master data management
Familiarity with governance frameworks such as DAMA DMBoK and maturity models
Technical expertise in data engineering, modelling, and integration technologies
Ability to influence and collaborate across diverse teams with competing priorities
Strong analytical skills to address complex data challenges
A passion for capability building - mentoring data stewards and fostering a data-aware culture

You're not just a planner—you're a doer. You understand that real impact comes from embedding governance into everyday work, and you're ready to lead that change.

At Evolution, as our name suggests, change and transformation is in our DNA. We want the Evolution experience to be your career highlight. We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a more inclusive and diverse workforce that represents the communities in which we operate. We provide a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all and candidates from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. We are focused on keeping our people safe and healthy and creating sustainable value in an environmentally and socially responsible way. Join our bold team to start your next exciting chapter.

Join a Queensland Government team responsible for enhancing and maintaining enterprise data warehouse and reporting capabilities. This role suits a multi-skilled BI Developer with strong experience across SQL Server, Visual Studio and the broader Microsoft BI stack.

You’ll design and deliver fit-for-purpose data models that put essential insights directly in the hands of business users, supporting the continued uplift and expansion of BI capability across the organisation.

Ad Text:
Maximize Capital Investment
Permanent role and make 2026 your year!
Flexible/Hybrid working

The Organisation

Airservices Australia is a government-owned organisation responsible for the safe and efficient management of 11% of the world’s airspace and provision of aviation rescue fire fighting services at Australia’s busiest airports.

Our people are our greatest asset with a dynamic and diverse team operating from locations across the country - from bustling cities to regional and remote locations, including an island. This team keep Australia’s aviation industry safe every day of the year, both in the air and on the ground.

We connect people with their world safely – linking family and friends, generating economic activity, creating jobs, and facilitating trade and tourism.

Airservices is committed to fostering a culture that is diverse, inclusive, and respectful.  We encourage motivated individuals who love what they do, value a service first mindset and embrace a challenge to explore a career with Airservices. In return you will be a valued team member, be offered flexibility and experience a meaningful career in an exciting, ever-evolving aviation industry.

The Role and the Team

In this role, you will:

Collaborate with stakeholders to understand business problems and opportunities, applying analytical techniques to define needs and inform executive decision-making. 
Maintain a deep understanding of the current state of service delivery operations within Airservices, including existing technology profiles, staffing and operational risks and opportunities.  
Define, evaluate and validate potential options (including as a result of cost increases), dependencies and strategic implications with key stakeholder, to address identified needs and risks, and communicate these through presentation of information and data to senior decision-makers. 

This is a senior leadership role and will be part of the Capital Portfolio Management team leadership group.

Please see the link below to view the full Position Description:

 Needs and Optioneering Advisor PD .pdf

The Person

A data-driven problem solver with a passion for turning complex information into clear, actionable insights you thrive in a collaborative environment.

With your ability to communicate with confidence and influence decisions at all levels you are seen as the “go to person”. Your ability to combine technical expertise with strategic thinking makes you a trusted advisor.

What You Will Bring

10 years + experience in strategic planning leading initiative development and contributing towards the creation and realisation of annual capital investment plans. 
Financial acumen and experience in investment prioritisation.  
Experience from ideation through to delivery to understand the nuances required to build robust Investment Cases.  
Exposure to large infrastructure, technology and construction projects. 

Experience: 5 to 10+ years experience in investment management and/or service/operation planning and/or infrastructure project managements and/or infrastructure/service optioneering/value engineering.

Skills: Expertise in stakeholder management, optioneering/problem solving and strong communication. 

Qualifications: Tertiary degree in Mathematics, Engineering, Computer Science, IT/Information Management, and/or equivalent experience in ATC or major infrastructure.

Attributes: Analytical mindset, adaptability, and the ability to deliver high-quality work under pressure.

Airservices Australia is a diverse and inclusive employer that recognises the benefits of having a workforce that reflects the communities in which we work. We encourage applications from diverse groups including Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander people.

Security Clearance

To be eligible to apply, you must be an Australian citizen or permanent resident as an Australian Government Baseline Security Clearance is required for this role. Please refer to the security check requirements successful applicants will be required to undertake as part of the recruitment process.

Should you require any further information please contact Christine Collins TA Partner at Christine.collins@airservicesaustralia.com

How to Apply

To apply for this position please lodge an application including a Cover Letter and CV online before Applications close 12noon (AEST) Friday 21 November 2025.

15 month engagement
Locations: QLD, WA, ACT, VIC, NSW, NT, SA, TAS
Ability to obtain a security clearance
Candidate must be an Australian citizen

Key duties and responsibilities

Design dimensional models (star/snowflake schemas) for business applications and reporting solutions that support forecasting, trend analysis, and performance metrics.
Ensure data models align with Microsoft best practices, particularly within Power BI and SQL Server environments.
Collaborate with data engineers, software developers, data analysts, and business stakeholders to translate requirements into scalable data models.
Maintain metadata repositories and data dictionaries in line with data and application governance standards.
Optimise model performance for large-scale datasets and complex queries or application data access requirements.
Contribute to the development of semantic models in Power BI.
Documenting data models, definitions and ETL data mapping rules.
Following the Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe) methodology for software development and contributing to Agile ceremonies.
Adhering to coding best practices and code quality standards including version control, code documentation, and testing.

Essential criteria

Proven experience in dimensional modelling and analytical modelling in enterprise environments..
Strong proficiency in Microsoft SQL Server, Azure Data Services and Power BI.
Deep understanding of data warehousing principles, ETL processes, and BI architecture.
Ability to communicate complex data concepts to technical and non-technical audiences.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, able to work effectively with diverse and geographically dispersed teams.

Desirable criteria

Familiarity with Microsoft Azure, SQL Server and emerging data tools in the Microsoft ecosystem.
Prior experience in federal government data domains.
Bachelor's or Master's degree in a relevant field (e.g. Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, Engineering).

Adairs & The Opportunity

Adairs is embarking on a huge transformation to become Australia’s Ultimate Home Style Destination.  This is an exciting time to come on board as we enter a new phase of growth and innovation. As our Senior Data Engineer you will lead the design, build and optimisation of our data ecosystem. In this role, you’ll shape our modern data platform, drive best-practice engineering and play an instrumental part in our data transformation roadmap.


How you will spend your day

Data Pipelines & Integration

Design, build and maintain scalable pipelines using Azure Data Factory, Databricks and Microsoft Fabric
Ensure high-quality, reliable data through monitoring, automation and optimisation
Partner with analysts, engineers and business teams to deliver the right data at the right time

Data Warehousing & Modelling

Lead the development of ETL processes (SSIS) from legacy SQL Server environments
Build dimensional models and schemas to support analytics and enterprise reporting
Ensure data structures meet evolving business needs

Data Migration & Modernisation

Drive the migration to modern data lake and warehouse platforms
Ensure minimal disruption, data integrity and a seamless transition
Collaborate across teams to deliver a scalable, future-ready data landscape

Governance, Security & Automation

Champion data quality, governance, accessibility and security
Implement access controls, encryption and masking for sensitive data
Integrate pipelines with CI/CD, automation and DevOps practices


About You

5+ years in data engineering, warehousing and ETL development
Advanced capability in Azure Data Factory, Databricks, Microsoft Fabric, SSIS and SQL Server
Strong skills in Python, SQL and scripting (PowerShell/Bash)
Deep experience in data modelling, governance and best practice
A collaborative communicator who translates technical work into business value
Degree in Computer Science, IT or similar (post-grad is a bonus)
Experience with agile and DevOps practices highly regarded
Microsoft certifications desirable


Make Home Your Career

Our people are everything to us, and we’re big believers in making our workplace fun and energising. It’s why we provide the following tools and benefits to help you thrive in your role.

We are all about collaboration and connection here at Adairs, so our team do work from the office 4 days a week with the option to work from home 1 day (if you choose):

A passionate team who love what they do and are great at it
Access to our infamous sample sales
Awesome team discounts 50% off full price styles, 15% off sale styles and free shipping

Access to a wellness program which includes free events to help you achieve a healthy work-life balance

Apply now and play a key role in shaping our next-generation data platform.

We’ve been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with over 115,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you’ll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you’ll also get to see your impact.

About the team

Our Commercial team is a large, but a close-knit group of trading experts, who are ready to shape the future of Coles. We pride ourselves on the long-lasting supplier relationships we build, the new ideas we develop and how passionately we work to help Australian eat and live better every day. And the best part? We’re all so different. We bring diversity of thought, backgrounds, and experience to every Business Unit across Coles Supermarkets and Liquor.

About the Role

We’re seeking a strategic leader to join our Own Brand team as Senior Performance & Delivery Manager. Reporting to the Head of Brand Performance & Innovation, you’ll lead a team of four (two Performance Managers and two Delivery Managers) to drive insights, strategy, and transformation across one of the most critical parts of our business, Own Brand.

This role is all about turning data into meaningful outputs that inform decisions at the highest level. You’ll prepare executive packs, steerco materials, and board papers, ensuring our leadership team has the insights they need to identify growth opportunities, mitigate risks, and understand why certain lines do or do not succeed.

You’ll also:

Lead group-level Own Brand performance reporting and insights to support strategic decisions
Manage board-level reporting, scorecards, and dashboards linking brand, product, financial, and customer outcomes
Oversee business case development and strategy papers for portfolio growth and innovation prioritisation
Design and deliver transformative change programs across Own Brand, ensuring alignment with strategic direction
Act as a key partner to senior leaders, influencing strategy through robust evidence and recommendations
Lead, coach, and develop a team of analysts and delivery managers, fostering a culture of data-driven decision-making

About you and your skills

Our ideal candidate is a strategic thinker with a consultancy mindset, who thrives in fast-paced, complex environments. You’re comfortable presenting to GMs and senior leaders, and you know how to craft compelling narratives from data. With strong project management skills and experience in strategy and transformation, you can identify trends, risks, and opportunities that drive growth. You’re confident preparing executive packs and board papers, and you bring a commercial lens to everything you do.

You’ll also ideally have:

Tertiary qualification in Business, Economics, Finance, or related discipline
Consultancy background highly regarded
Extensive experience in business performance, strategy, or transformation roles (FMCG/retail preferred)
Advanced analytical and financial modelling skills
Strong program management and change delivery experience
Excellent stakeholder engagement and influencing skills at senior levels

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Ad Text:
About UNSW

At UNSW, we pride ourselves on being a workplace where the best people come to do their best work.  We aspire to be Australia’s global university, improving and transforming lives through excellence in research, outstanding education and a commitment to advancing a just society. 

Why your role matters

The Data Risk Manager leads UNSW’s enterprise-wide approach to data risk, operating with significant independence to design and oversee the frameworks, policies, and controls that protect the University’s data assets. The role provides authoritative guidance to senior governance bodies, shaping institutional decision-making and embedding accountability for data resilience, compliance, and responsible data use across all faculties and divisions.

Acting as UNSW’s primary expert on data risk, the position works closely with Enterprise Risk, Compliance, IT Security, Legal, and external regulators to ensure integrated, sector-leading practice in data governance. The role reports to the Program Manager and may oversee direct reports.

About the Role               

The successful applicant will be required to undertake and have experience in the following areas of expertise:

Lead UNSW’s enterprise-wide data risk strategy, embedding resilience, compliance, and responsible data use across operations and culture.
Establish and maintain frameworks, policies, and standards that set sector-leading benchmarks for data risk management.
Provide authoritative advice and assurance to the University Executive, Council committees, and divisional leaders on high-impact data risks and compliance.
Oversee monitoring, visibility, and escalation of significant emerging data risks, ensuring timely mitigation and governance reporting.
Direct implementation of controls for privacy, security, data quality, and compliance in collaboration with IT Security, Legal, and Enterprise Risk.
Manage executive-level response to major data incidents, ensuring accountability, remediation, and systemic improvements.
Drive organisational ownership, capability building, and cultural change in data risk, representing UNSW in national and international forums.

About You

Tertiary qualification in risk or information management, or equivalent experience.
Extensive expertise in data governance, privacy, information security, records management, and higher education regulatory frameworks.
Proven ability to design and implement enterprise-wide data risk frameworks, policies, and controls.
Experience operationalising the Three Lines of Defence model at scale.
Strong track record influencing executive decision-making and providing authoritative advice to governance bodies.
Excellent stakeholder engagement and influencing skills, driving accountability across academic and professional groups.
Advanced analytical, assurance, and reporting skills, with expertise in risk management/audit methodologies (e.g., ISO 31000, NIST, COBIT, ISO/IEC 27001) and commitment to UNSW’s objectives.

For further information on the role & responsibilities, please refer to the Position Description

How to Apply: Submit your CV & cover letter detailing your interest and suitability for the job (as per the skills & experience bullet points in the Position Description) before Sunday 7 December by 11:55pm.


Please note: Sponsorship is not available for this role, valid Australian working rights are required on application.

UNSW Benefits and Culture: People are at the core of everything we do. We recognise it is the contributions of our staff who make UNSW one of the best universities in Australia and the world. Our benefits include: 

Flexible Working Options (work from home, flexible hours etc) 
Additional 3 days leave during December festive period.
Career development opportunities 
Up to 50% discount on UNSW courses
Flexible 17% Superannuation contributions, additional leave-loading payments and salary sacrifice.
Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness passport)

AJQ Consulting is a leading provider in the delivery of Information Technology & Professional Services.

Our success is built on our team.

We aim to provide our team with meaningful projects to work on where they can stretch their minds and showcase their expertise. With our growth mindset including customer-centric approach, we add value to our communities and to our clients’ outcomes.

We are proud to be supporting government initiatives across multiple sectors which has a direct impact on our communities’ experience.

We have partnered with a Federal Government Agency on a digital transformation initiative and are looking to place a Senior SQL Geospatial Analyst to join our team on a 12 months contract basis with a possibility to extend.

The role can be based in any state, Hybrid working is required.

About the role:

Geospatial and geographic information systems (GIS) engineers work at the intersection of cartography, programming and data analysis. They analyse spatial data analysis and engineering.

You will be tasked with spatial mapping data assets and calculation functions for integration with business applications supporting election management business processes.

The role is responsible for undertaking work that is moderately complex to complex and/or sensitive in nature, under limited direction, utilising expertise and knowledge within the geospatial domain.

Responsibilities:

Conduct technical design for geospatial related matters and provide technical insight and recommendations regarding spatial data and spatial engineering techniques and approaches.

Responsible for preparation of appropriate documentation such as design specifications, user guides and handover documentation.

Develop and maintain geospatial data assets and functions as part of a multi-disciplinary team of application developers, data engineers and business analysts.

Communicate the insights from GIS data to technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Good understanding of master and metadata concepts.

Design and implement geospatial solutions using SQL Server spatial data types (geometry and geography).

Develop and optimise spatial queries to support location-based services and analytics.

Integrate geospatial data with Azure Maps for routing, distance calculations, and spatial visualizations.

Build APIs and services that consume Azure Maps for real-time geospatial insights.

Collaborate with architects and analysts to define geospatial solution scope and data flows.

Maintain and enhance geospatial databases, ensuring performance and scalability.

Document geospatial integration patterns and provide technical support for Azure Maps usage 

Requirements:

5+ years’ experience with GIS software development and Cloud solutions.

Demonstrated ability to deliver Geospatial solutions and support through the System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) and Agile development practices and processes including Azure Enterprise Cloud.

Strong proficiency in SQL Server spatial functions (e.g., STDistance, STIntersects).

Experience with Azure Maps REST APIs and SDKs.

Familiarity with Azure Function Apps or Logic Apps for lightweight geospatial processing.

Understanding of coordinate systems, spatial indexing, and data formats like GeoJSON and WKT

Must hold baseline clearance.

Applicants located outside of Canberra will be required to travel to Canberra for operational reasons as directed (e.g. onboarding, planning exercises [1-2 times per quarter], in person training, etc.). Any required travel will be discussed in advance and notice given wherever practicable.

We're seeking a commercially astute Senior Finance Business Partner (FBP) to provide strategic financial leadership to our Information Technology Division. This role is pivotal in supporting IT leaders to make informed investment decisions across infrastructure, applications, services, and cloud initiatives. As a trusted advisor, you will shape financial outcomes by delivering deep analysis, robust business cases, and actionable insights that enable smarter technology investments, improved vendor management, and greater value from the IT portfolio.

If you are looking for a role that delivers financial insights and analysis to enable profitable growth and strategic decision-making apply today!

Responsibilities

Partner with senior IT leaders across key categories — hardware, software/applications, services, and cloud — providing financial insight and commercial advice.

Support development and review of business cases for major information technology investments, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities and financial governance.

Partner with procurement and IT to drive vendor rationalisation, pricing analysis, and supplier performance management.

Deliver accurate and insightful reporting, highlighting run-rate trends, project spend, and return on investment.
Support forecasts and monthly performance reviews, ensuring transparency and accountability in IT financials.

Skills & Experience

Tertiary qualification and CPA/CA essential.
Strong financial partnering experience with Information Technology teams.
Deep understanding of IT financial categories — hardware, software/applications, services, cloud.
Sound knowledge of capitalisation principles for technology projects, including SaaS and cloud treatment.
Proven experience supporting business case development, benefits realisation, and project accounting.
Strong commercial acumen and analytical capability, with the ability to translate complex IT and financial information into actionable insights.
Experience in supplier or vendor analysis, including pricing and contract performance review.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills — able to influence senior technology and finance leaders.
Highly proficient in Excel and ERP/reporting systems (e.g. SAP, Oracle, TM1, Power BI).

We’ve been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with over 115,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you’ll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you’ll also get to see your impact.

About the team

Strategy is making the future of retail a reality. We’re a big business with big ideas. Our team works together with all our business units to help bring those ideas to life. We stay focused on what’s next, so we can make our customers’ experiences even better now and lead the industry for years to come.

About the role

A permanent opportunity exists for a dynamic Strategy Business Partner (SBP) to join our Group Strategy function. In this pivotal role, you will partner with senior stakeholders to shape and execute Coles’ strategic priorities, ensuring we remain a world class retailer. You’ll play a critical role in turning insights into action, supporting decision making at the highest level, and driving initiatives that deliver long-term value. Your key responsibilities will include:

Deliver fact-based insights to inform business strategies, the corporate plan, and solutions to critical challenges. 
Partner with Strategy Managers and the Head of Group Strategy to design and execute Coles’ strategy. 
Apply structured problem solving and rigorous analysis to develop initiatives and define success metrics for strategic issues. 
Act as a strategic thought partner to senior stakeholders, driving execution of key initiatives. 
Conduct high quality quantitative and qualitative analysis to solve complex business problems. 
Synthesise findings into clear recommendations that enable effective execution. 
Take ownership of project success within your area of responsibility, ensuring timely and impactful delivery. 
Identify risks to in scope projects and support the development of mitigation plans. 

About you and your skills


You are a strategic thinker with strong analytical capabilities, able to turn complexity into clarity and influence senior stakeholders with confidence. You will bring

Previous experience in management consulting (ideally MBB), investment banking, or retail strategy. 
Proven expertise in complex analytical problem solving (e.g., hypothesis-based approaches). 
Advanced proficiency in financial modelling and tools such as PowerPoint and Excel. 
Experience managing work streams within large scale projects. 
Ability to craft and contribute to board-level presentations and reports. 
Strong communication and presentation skills with senior stakeholders. 
Experience collaborating across cross-functional business units. 
A track record of thriving in high performance team environments. 

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Your new company

Join a major organisation driving a large-scale data modernisation program. This project focusses on replatforming analytics and migrating data from legacy systems to a modern Microsoft Fabric environment. You'll be part of a high-performing team delivering critical outcomes for business and research stakeholders.

Your new role

As a Business Analyst, you will play a key role in gathering and translating requirements for complex data and analytics initiatives. Acting as a bridge between business and technical teams, you'll ensure successful delivery of project milestones and support the transition to BAU. Key responsibilities include:

Eliciting and documenting data requirements from diverse stakeholders
Translating business needs into actionable technical specifications and user stories
Coordinating with internal DevOps teams and external vendors
Managing Jira stories and supporting risk and issue resolution
Assisting with change management and stakeholder communications


What you'll need to succeed

Proven experience in Business Analysis within data, BI, or analytics projects
Ability to act as Product Owner and manage backlog in Jira
Strong understanding of data concepts: ingestion, modelling, quality, and pipelines
Excellent stakeholder engagement and vendor coordination skills
Familiarity with Jira and Confluence (essential); SAS and Microsoft Fabric (advantageous)


What you'll get in return

This is an 11-month contract with an immediate start for the right candidate. You will work as part of a dedicated and collaborative team and work on a high-impact project.

What you need to do now

If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call us now.

If this job isn't quite right for you, but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion about your career.

Hello. We're Virgin Australia. We're the airline that's always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We're on a mission to make flying better than 'nice'. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety -- in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you'll be doing:

This Senior Associate, Strategy & Planning position is a newly created role to support our new, Integrated Planning team that is part of our Strategy & Transformation division. You will play a pivotal role in supporting Virgin Australia's Integrated Planning transformation by analysing strategic planning scenarios, operational and schedule planning processes, uncovering efficiency opportunities, and developing strategic insights. You'll work independently on strategic planning analyses across multiple time horizons, from seasonal schedule planning to long-term strategic questions.

Leveraging your analytical expertise and technical skills, you'll create data-driven insights that support Virgin Australia's transition to new planning cycles, moving beyond traditional network design to focus on operational execution excellence. This role offers a unique opportunity to make a significant impact on our company's success as we continue our exciting growth journey!

Further responsibilities:

This role requires sharp analytical skills, structured problem-solving capabilities, and the ability to understand complex operational systems
You'll translate operational, commercial, and competitor data into strategic insights and evaluate planning trade-offs
Communicate recommendations clearly to stakeholders from front-line operations to executive leadership
Your work will directly inform strategic planning decisions that improve our on-time performance, reduce costs, support sustainable growth, and shape our long-term strategic direction
Conduct advanced financial and operational modelling for planning initiatives
Collaborate with cross-divisional teams on analytics projects to advance integrated planning capabilities
Structure ambiguous operational or strategic problems, to create a hypothesis and then work independently to find a favourable solution to recommend to the business

You'll be great in this role if you have

A degree in Commerce, Economics, Mathematics, Engineering, or a related field
3–4 years’ experience in management consulting (MBB preferred), investment banking, corporate strategy, or operational improvement
Experience structuring ambiguous operational or strategic problems and driving to solutions independently (structured problem-solving and hypothesis-driven thinking)
Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills. You can navigate ambiguity, work across large datasets, and distil complexity into clarity
Advanced Excel modelling and data analysis skills
Strong communication and storytelling ability, with experience developing executive-level presentations that drive decisions
A proactive, self-starter mindset with the ability to juggle multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment

What you'll get from us

We're committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry -- including (but not limited to):

Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (plus $1000 travel credits per year)
Flexible and hybrid working, with a mix of working from home and the office
'Dress for Your Day' -- wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you
One of Brisbane's most admired office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, lunch options, the Busway nearby, a rooftop restaurant, onsite gym and South Bank across the road
Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide
Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services
Free counselling and online tools to support your physical, mental, social and financial health

When everyone is included, everyone wins

We're all individuals. And we love that. That's why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTIQ+ community, and anyone else who wants to join us.

Ready to apply?

Working at Virgin Australia isn't just a job. It's a passion that becomes part of you. Are you ready to join us? Get ready for a rewarding experience. Apply today!

Company: Australian Institute of Health and Welfare
Ad Text:
The Australian Institute of Health and Welfare (AIHW) is Australia’s authoritative source of health and welfare data and analysis. As an independent national information and statistics agency within the Commonwealth’s Health portfolio, the AIHW publishes more than 400 data products each year, maintains and administers specialised national data standards and classifications, and supports high quality research.

AIHW are seeking to fill two roles:

- Group Head – Population Health Group SES Band 1; and

- Group Head – Housing and Specialised Services Group, SES Band 1.

The AIHW has recently established 3 divisions - the Health Insights Division, Community and First Nations Insights Division and the Corporate Strategy and Performance Division. Currently, Group Head vacancies exist in the Health Insights Division (for the Population Health Group), and the Community and First Nations Insights Division (for the Housing and Specialised Services Group). Both these roles report to Executive Directors (SES Band 2) and form part of the institute’s senior leadership team.

The Population Health Group comprises several units covering burden of disease, cancer, chronic conditions, preventive health and injuries. The group collects, compiles, analyses and presents comprehensive data about the health of Australians. The group has a particular role to play in expanding the amount of evidence available, particularly in relation to cancer and linkage across domains such as aged care and disability.

The Housing and Specialised Services Group comprises several units that collect and analyse data to support reporting and policy decisions on the health and welfare of Australians. The Group has a particular focus on specialised services including housing, veterans supports, drug and alcohol supports, child protection systems, youth justice systems and correctional facilities.

To be a strong contender for either of these important roles you will have experience leading data management, analytical, reporting and/or statistical functions and have a strong working understanding of the Australian health and welfare landscape. You will excel in working in complex environments and you will be forward thinking, innovative and adept at building relationships across a broad range of sectors. Your integrity, judgement and strong leadership credentials will be paramount. Your impressive personal style and ability to engender trust and respect will be complemented by intellectual rigor, critical analysis, and first class communication and presentation skills.

For further information on the eligibility requirements, selection criteria and how to apply please visit the AIHW careers page and download the position description. If, after reading the selection documentation, you require further information please contact Tricia Searson or Karina Duffey at Executive Intelligence Group on (02) 6232 2200.

Applications close: 11.30pm AEDT 30 November 2025.
